text.tspan: N.B. if background through L4, not the same story
increase in firing rate from V1 to V2 because of the lower strength of the Inh->Exc coupling in V2
the CB1->L4 inhibition has the ability to shutdown evoked activity in L4, this removing input-driven correlations
decrease in firing rate from V2 to V2-CB1-KO because of the higher strength of the Inh->Exc coupling in V2-CB1-KO
the lower excitabilty of the V2 network induces a lower CB1->L4 inhibition (both spontaneous and evoked), thus allowing to increase
the evoked L4 activity and thus to re-create the input-driven correlations that disappeared in the V2 case
